associatoR 0.1.0.9

Cluster stability

Source: R/cluster.R
ar_cluster_stability.Rd

ar_cluster_stability evaluates the stability of a clustering generated by ar_cluster_targets()

Usage

ar_cluster_stability(associations, n_boot = 1000, unique = FALSE)

Arguments

associations

an associatoR object including target_embeddings.

n_boot

an integer specifying the number of bootstrap samples to draw. Default is 1000.

unique

a logical specifying whether duplicate targets in bootstrap shouod be ignored. Default is TRUE.

Value

The function returns a list containing two matrices with the target- (target_stability) and cluster-wise (cluster_stability) probabilities of being assigned to the same cluster under random pertubation.

Details

Clustering stability is calculated with the identical clustering settings (e.g., clustering algorithm, similarity function, etc.) used to generate the original cluster assignment. The information is stored as a attribute to the targets table with name "cluster_settings".

Examples

ar_obj = ar_import(intelligence,
                   participant = participant_id,
                   cue = cue,
                   response = response,
                   participant_vars = c(gender, education),
                   response_vars = c(response_position, response_level)) %>%
  ar_set_targets(targets = "cues") %>%
  ar_embed_targets() %>%
  ar_cluster_targets(method = "louvain")
#> Warning: 204 targets with count < min_count were dropped from embedding.

ar_cluster_stability(ar_obj, n_boot = 10)
